      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the caution part but i feel like the doctors always play it too safe with these things. i've seen people in biohacking groups doing way more than that and they seem totally fine. if i'm only doing it for like 6 weeks to get through the darkest part of winter, isn't the risk of toxicity basically zero? like most people's bodies can handle a temporary spike right?",
